cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.NI, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a discrete variant of the HRG model and discusses algorithmic properties of regularly generated triangulations.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the HRG model is commonly used in social network analysis and the paper presents experimental results conducted on real world networks.
- cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) is a possibility as the paper discusses algorithms for working with the proposed model.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possibility as the HRG model has applications in internet routing and the paper discusses the practical benefits of the proposed model.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possibility as the paper discusses a graph model and its algorithmic properties.
